{
  "message": "fuzz(wal-replay): 17 structured seeds for header & commit decoders\n\nfuzz_wal_replay exercises three sibling decoders on the same input:\nffs_mvcc::wal::decode_header (16-byte WAL file header), decode_commit\n(record_len|body|crc commit framing), and commit_byte_size (framing\npre-flight). Existing corpus had 3 ad-hoc seeds (single byte, empty,\nheader bytes) that exercised only the simplest paths.\n\nAdds 17 seeds spanning every documented branch:\n\n  WAL header decoder:\n  * valid default header\n  * valid header with non-zero reserved bytes (must still parse \u2014\n    the decoder ignores reserved)\n  * bad magic, unsupported version, unsupported checksum type\n  * 15-byte truncated header (InsufficientData)\n\n  Commit decoder happy paths (with correctly-computed CRC32C):\n  * empty commit (no writes, MIN_COMMIT_RECORD_SIZE = 29 bytes)\n  * one tiny write\n  * three writes with varying block numbers and data lengths\n  * one 64-byte write payload\n\n  Commit decoder error paths:\n  * CRC byte flipped (Corrupted branch)\n  * zero record_len + non-zero tail (Corrupted: \"preallocated tail\n    must be all zero\")\n  * zero record_len + all-zero tail (EndOfData sentinel \u2014 the legal\n    end-of-WAL marker)\n  * record_len smaller than MIN_COMMIT_RECORD_SIZE-4 (Corrupted)\n  * record_len near u32::MAX (NeedMore-with-overflow guard)\n\n  Cross-decoder shapes:\n  * valid header followed by valid commit (realistic WAL prefix \u2014\n    decode_header succeeds AND decode_commit hits NeedMore on its\n    second pass since the bytes-after-header don't start with a\n    record-length, exercising both happy and error branches)\n  * 3 bytes (decode_commit's NeedMore(4) and decode_header's\n    InsufficientData fire simultaneously)\n\nValidated by an 11 s libFuzzer run: 3.7 M executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
